"title": "6740: returning to God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6740",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture declares that all humanity has turned away from God, and must return to him. The term “repentance” is often used to refer to this process of returning to God and the inward and outward changes that it demands of people. Scripture also indicates that believers can wander away from God; they too must return to him.</p>\n<h2>All people have turned away from God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:6\">ISA 53:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:6\">ISA 64:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job25:4\">JOB 25:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:9\">JER 17:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:19\">JHN 3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:23\">ROM 3:23</a></p>\n<h2>Wayward people must return to God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:22\">ISA 44:22</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos14:1\">HOS 14:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech1:3\">ZEC 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:9\">2CH 30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:9\">NEH 1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:23\">JOB 22:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer24:7\">JER 24:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:40\">LAM 3:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:1\">HOS 6:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:6\">HOS 12:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:12\">JOL 2:12</a></p>\n<h2>Means of returning to God</h2>\n<h3>Realisation of estrangement from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:40\">LAM 3:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:5\">1SA 24:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:10\">2SA 24:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:29-2Chr6:31\">2CH 6:29–6:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:20\">ROM 3:20</a></p>\n<h3>Acknowledgment of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:3\">PSA 51:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:27\">EXO 9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:39-Num14:40\">NUM 14:39–14:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:34\">NUM 22:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:20\">JOS 7:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:24-1Sam15:25\">1SA 15:24–15:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:3-Matt27:4\">MAT 27:3–27:4</a></p>\n<h3>Sorrow for sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:18\">PSA 38:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:1-Ps51:2\">PSA 51:1–51:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:9-2Cor7:10\">2CO 7:9–7:10</a></p>\n<h3>A sense of guilt for sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:10\">2SA 24:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:5-Ezra9:6\">EZR 9:5–9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:1-Ps38:4\">PSA 38:1–38:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:17-Ps38:18\">PSA 38:17–38:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:3\">PSA 51:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:37-Acts2:38\">ACT 2:37–2:38</a></p>\n<h3>Repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:27\">ISA 1:27</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:37-Acts2:38\">ACT 2:37–2:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:20\">ISA 59:20</a></p>\n<h2>A parable of returning to God</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:11-Luke15:24\">LUK 15:11–15:24</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of people returning to God</h2>\n<p>Israelites:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:15\">JDG 10:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr15:4\">2CH 15:4</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:13-2Sam12:14\">2SA 12:13–12:14</a> <em>David</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:5-Jonah3:10\">JON 3:5–3:10</a> <em>the people of Nineveh</em></p>",
